<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="595" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/287</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice President of the American International
                                    Corp</hi>. (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tinsley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New
                                            York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March 23,
                                        1918</hi>.</date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received March
                                        25.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honour to lay before the
                                Department, for its information, certain correspondence showing the
                                measures the Corporation is prepared to take with reference to the
                                improvement of the Grand Canal in China.</p>
                            <p>The Corporation would greatly appreciate it if the Department will be
                                good enough to inform the Legation at Peking, by mail, of the
                                substance of this correspondence, and begs to thank the Department
                                now for its compliance with this request.<note n="44" xml:id="d595fn44">Correspondence not printed; it was transmitted
                                    to the Minister in China, in instruction No. 780, Mar. 28,
                                    1918.</note></p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. P.
                                Tinsley</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>